LOCUS       phiC31_attP              100 bp    DNA              UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  phiC31_attP — 100 bp phage attachment site (attP) of Streptomyces
            phage phiC31, recognized by the phiC31 large serine integrase;
            contains the minimal 39 bp core with two 9 bp inverted-repeat
            half-sites and the central TT crossover..
